==Abstract==

This IIP defines derivation paths for multisig wallets using SHA3-based HD derivation. It is adapted from BIP 48 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Multisig wallets require standardized derivation paths to ensure interoperability between different wallet implementations.

==Specification==

===Derivation Path===

<pre>
m / purpose' / coin_type' / account' / script_type' / change / address_index
</pre>

Where:
* purpose = 48 (multisig)
* coin_type = 2210 (INTcoin)
* account = account index
* script_type = script type identifier
* change = 0 (external) or 1 (internal)
* address_index = address index

===Script Types===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Type !! Value !! Description
|-
| P2WSH || 2 || Native multisig
|}

Note: INTcoin only supports native (Bech32m) addresses.

===Example Paths===

First external address of first P2WSH multisig account:
<pre>
m/48'/2210'/0'/2'/0/0
</pre>

First change address:
<pre>
m/48'/2210'/0'/2'/1/0
</pre>

===Extended Public Key Export===

For multisig coordination, export the extended public key at:
<pre>
m/48'/2210'/account'/script_type'
</pre>

This allows deriving all addresses without exposing private keys.

